  "text": "On the other hand, there are grounds for claiming that WCF may be worthwhile for young learners. There is evidence that children do in fact have the ability to attend to form. In oral corrective feedback studies, where the feedback has been made explicit (e.g. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , a positive effect on young children's acquisition of grammar has been reported. Given that WCF is invariably explicit in nature, it is possible that children will attend to it, at least sometimes, and be able to utilize what they have learned from it in their subsequent writing.",
